claim.claim-text:
1. A process for treating used absorbent sanitary products, comprising the steps of:
providing a rotary cylindrical autoclave having an inner surface and two ends;
opening a hatch disposed on the cylindrical autoclave to enable access to the cylindrical autoclave, wherein the hatch may be sealably closed to enable pressurization of the cylindrical autoclave;
loading the cylindrical autoclave with absorbent sanitary products;
heating to a sterilization temperature and pressurizing the cylindrical autoclave and at the same time driving the cylindrical autoclave in rotation about a longitudinal axis thereof; and
providing inside the cylindrical autoclave a plurality of high-density unsecured tearing elements designed to facilitate thermal and physical destructuring of the absorbent sanitary products.
